FT  01 JUN 93 / Observer: Legal device
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mary Arden, the QC who was recently made a judge, seems suddenly to have
changed her title. As a senior legal counsel, she was always referred to as
Miss. Now on the bench, she has become a Mrs. Confusingly, she is married,
but has always retained her maiden name as a trade name.
Apparently judges cannot be referred to as Miss, the joke being that they
are all married - at least to the law.
