FT  01 JUN 93 / International Company News: ICI demerger leads to changes in
FT-SE Actuaries Share Indices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
As a result of the prospective demerger of ICI and Zeneca, which will come
into effect today, all constituents of the FT-SE 100 have been ranked by
size.
Both ICI and Zeneca will be included in the FT-SE 100 Index, while English
China Clays, the smallest capitalised constituent at close of trading
Friday, has been removed from the FT-SE 100 Index.
English China Clays will become a constituent of the FT-SE Mid 250 Index.
Owners Abroad, the smallest capitalised constituent at close of trading, has
been removed from the FT-SE Mid 250 Index; it will become a constituent of
the FT-SE SmallCap Index.
No companies will be removed from the FT-SE SmallCap.
When the demerger of ICI and Zeneca comes into effect, ICI will remain a
constituent of the Financial Times Ordinary Share Index (the '30 Share').
