<HEADLINE>
FT  01 JUN 93 / Construction Contracts: Upgrading football club
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
WIMPEY CONSTRUCTION has won a Pounds 5m design and build contract to
redevelop the south stand at West Ham United Football Club in east London.
With the football season drawn to a close and West Ham promoted to the
Premier League, Wimpey has started work at Upton Park to upgrade the ground.
Rebuilding the south stand will nearly double the seating capacity of the
stadium creating an additional 7,650 seats.
The steel-framed, two-tier stand will be topped with a 36 metre wide roof
which will be supported by a 73 metre goal post lattice beam running the
length of the stand. As the roof is only propped by columns at each end of
the stand, spectators will have an unobstructed view of the pitch.
The profile of the lower tier follows a parabolic shape which also maximises
the crowd's view of a match.
Situated between the two levels, Wimpey is building 19 executive boxes with
full catering facilities for up to 200 people. Facilities include club
offices and a lounge for the use of supporters. Wimpey's design team is AD
Consultants as architect and Jan Bobrowski as structural engineer.
</TEXT>
