<HEADLINE>
FT  01 JUN 93 / Management (The Growing Business): Liberal Democrats unveil
six-point plan - In A Nutshell
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Liberal Democrats last week unveiled a six-point programme to back small
businesses.
The programme calls for a government subsidy for bank loans to small and
medium-sized manufacturing companies; grants for innovative small businesses
in high-technology areas; and government subsidy for private-sector regional
venture capital funds which back start-ups. It also urges the banks and
government support agencies to offer equity finance, for a study of the use
of mutal guarantee schemes by groups of businesses and for a statutory right
to interest on unpaid debts.
