<HEADLINE>
FT  01 JUN 93 / Deputy chairman of GA dies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
ROBERT ADAM, deputy chairman of General Accident, died last week aged 70.
After training as a chartered accountant he joined British Petroleum in
1950. Subsequently he became one of the leading figures in the oil industry.
After retiring from BP in 1983 he became a director of MEPC, the property
company, which he served as chairman between 1984 and 1988. He joined the
board of GA in 1980 and became deputy chairman in 1987.
