FT  01 JUN 93 / Union plea on nursery education
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SCHOOL STANDARDS will decline unless young children are given a head start
through nursery education, says the National Association of
Schoolmasters/Union of Women Teachers, the second-largest teachers' union.
The union yesterday urged MPs to support nursery education for all three and
four-year-olds in the same way as do other European Community countries, the
US, Canada, Australia and New Zealand.
Mr Nigel de Gruchy, NASUWT general secretary, said: 'The way to improve
school standards is to teach very young children. It is not good enough just
to mind them.'
