FT  01 JUN 93 / Teacher training initiative launched
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
FOUR secondary schools and two city technology colleges will pilot
school-based teacher training from September, Mr John Patten, education
secretary, said yesterday.
More than 150 student teacher places will be funded in this first phase of
the scheme to shift teacher training away from universities and into school
classrooms.
Successful students will be awarded qualified teacher status at the end of
their training.
