<HEADLINE>
FT  01 JUN 93 / Arts body may face strong criticism
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GARY MEAD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE NATIONAL Heritage Department is likely to publish this week findings
from a report which it is believed strongly criticises certain aspects of
Arts Council activities, Gary Mead writes.
The report, by management consultants Price Waterhouse, will be presented to
the council on Thursday. Its findings are likely to be made public the
following day.
The study is part of the government's attempts to bring greater efficiency
to the public sector through its market-testing programme, which looks into
ways the non-core activities of quangos can be hived off to the private
sector.
In the case of the Arts Council, which last year received Pounds 225m of
government money to distribute in support of the arts, the report is
believed to have considered how efficiently it has served the 10 regional
arts boards. Its grant is to be cut by Pounds 5m this year.
