<HEADLINE>
FT  01 JUN 93 / Rouble falls to Rbs1,024 to the dollar
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LEYLA BOULTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE rouble fell through the Rbs1,000-to-the-dollar barrier yesterday as part
of a relentless slide caused by inflationary expectations, loose monetary
policy and the government's inability to push through a credible economic
reform package, writes Leyla Boulton. The Russian currency yesterday fell to
Rbs1,024 to the dollar on the official currency exchange from Rbs994 last
week.
