FT  29 MAY 93 / International Company News: Cyrus Vance to mediate in O&amp;Y
unit's case
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AGENCIES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE Canadian administrator to Olympia &amp; York Developments, the financially
beleaguered Canadian developer, said the US Trustee has appointed Cyrus
Vance as the mediator to intercede between the administrator and the
creditors to O&amp;Y's US unit, agencies report from New York.
The appointment was made under this week's order by US Bankruptcy Court
Judge James Garrity. The mediator, called an 'examiner,' is charged with
working with the various parties to reach an agreement on an independent
board for the US unit, Olympia &amp; York Cos. (USA).
On May 24, Judge Garrity denied a motion by Citicorp, parent company of New
York's largest bank, to appoint a 'responsible officer' to run O&amp;Y's US
unit.
Citicorp and other unsecured creditors of the unit had wanted Mr John
Zucotti, president of the US offshoot,named as responsible officer as the
O&amp;Y subsidiary seeks to restructure its debt.
O&amp;Y (USA), an insolvent real estate concern, is attempting to restructure
Dollars 5.3bn of debt.
A spokeswoman for the administrator said Mr Vance is with the New York law
firm of Simpson Thatcher. Mr Vance also recently worked on negotiating a
peace agreement in war-torn Bosnia, in the former Yugoslavia.
Mr Vance served as US secretary of state under President Carter from 1977 to
1980. He then returned to his law practice at Simpson Thatcher &amp; Bartlett.
